An urn contains marbles of five colors: red, white, blue, green, and yellow. When five marbles are drawn without replacement, the following events have proportional probabilities:
(a) the selection of all five red marbles;
(b) the selection of one white and four red marbles;
(c) the selection of one white, one blue, and three red marbles;
(d) the selection of one white, one blue, one green, and two red marbles;
(e) the selection of one marble of each color.
Determine the smallest number of marbles in the urn that satisfies these conditions.
A) 30
B) 40
C) 55
D) 70
E) 100
